organic_results.title: Interpersonal relationships as mediators of structural effects: College student socialization in a traditional and an experimental university environment
organic_results.snippet: College student change on values, intellectual orientation, and personal development was analyzed in the context of a causal model. The research was based on a longitudinal panel study of students in a traditional, large liberal arts college, and a small, innovative, living-learning subenvironment. The results indicated that college impact on students in different environments was mediated through the process of human interaction with socializing agents.
